entries.player_3_2: It seems too simple. What's the catch?
entries.player_sorry_2: I'll keep working on the mission.
entries.player_reset_2: I don't want this mission right now.
entries.notit_2: These are not the codes I was supposed to get. You're not trying to cheat us, are you?
entries.gotowork_2: Where are those codes you were supposed to give me, friend?
entries.npc_smuggle_2: I'll make sure these get to our accounting department. You know Luthin spoke well of you. Keep up the good work and you may find yourself joining our extended family.
entries.npc_breech_2: Hey, buddy! Over here! You looking for some Corellian Double-Brandy?
entries.npc_failure_2: Failure to deliver some codes pretty much eliminates you from our list of
Maybe you should try moisture farming.
entries.npc_noloc_2: My superior should transmit his coordinates to me in just a few moments.
entries.npc_work_2: Did you deliver those codes yet? My superior, he doesn't like to wait.
entries.npc_reward_2: Now those are the kind of results our organization prizes, friend. I'll mention you to my boss. We may be in touch.
entries.npc_backtowork_2: I don't have anything else to tell you. You going or not?
entries.npc_4_2: There's a possibility that a few tough guys might try and take these codes away from you. Competitors, you understand. Nothing someone like you couldn't handle, though.
entries.npc_3_2: Eh, no big loss. There's plenty more candidates out there.
entries.npc_2_2: All right. Take these codes to a man named Gnurr Fenkel. He knows to expect you, so if he doesn't say,
when he sees you, blast him and bring the codes back to me.
entries.npc_1_2: You performed so well on that last job that I've decided to only give you one more test. Since you got us these bank codes, it only seems fair that you should be the one to deliver them to my superior. Seems simple enough, right? Can you do it?
entries.player_sorry_1: I'll keep working on the mission.
entries.player_reset_1: I don't want this mission right now.
entries.npc_breech_1: I knew Black Sun would be sending someone after me. Die, scum!
entries.npc_failure_1: Maybe you don't have what it takes to join our elite ranks. Don't sweat it, though, not everyone in the galaxy can be equally as competent.
entries.npc_noloc_1: I'll get you our former agent's coordinates in just a few moments.
entries.npc_work_1: Did you get those bank codes? Remember, I'm evaluating your performance.
entries.npc_reward_1: Not bad, not bad at all. Another performance like that and I may just recommend you to my employers.
entries.npc_backtowork_1: I've given you all the info you're going to get. Still interested?
entries.npc_4_1: The name of my organization is not something we should discuss until I've determined that you're a suitable candidate. You want to try and prove that?
entries.npc_3_1: Well, our organization is not for everybody. Take it easy, friend.
entries.npc_2_1: Great. I like your enthusiasm. Oh, and by the way, I doubt this client will give these codes up willingly so you may have to persuade him. To death. Best of luck.
entries.npc_1_1: Hey there, friend. I'm a recruiter, of sorts, on the lookout for promising young talent. I represent an organization that values ingenuity, loyalty, and above all, discretion. If this sounds intriguing, I have a little

for you, something to let me get a better understanding of your skills. A former agent left our organization owing us some money. Not a huge sum but enough to warrant a visit from someone like you. I doubt this individual has the money on him but what he does have are some bank codes that would assist our collection efforts. Can you bring me these codes?
entries.npc_reset: Follow-through is important in my line of work, buddy. Come back when you can give me that.
entries.cantwork: My assignments take a good deal of concentration. Come back when you can focus a bit more.
entries.next: I don't have anything more for you now, friend, but keep checking back with me. You never know when business will be booming again.
